  m_text: "A rectangular prism is a three-dimensional shape, having six faces, where
    all the faces (top, bottom, and lateral faces) of the prism are rectangles such
    that all the pairs of the opposite faces are congruent. A rectangular prism is
    also known as a cuboid. \n\n<b>Formula: <i>V = lwh </i></b> "
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 2e498d1c8094910479dc3e1b768306a4, type: 2}
